\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 INSTRUCTIONS FOR LOCAL SETUP AND GENERAL INFO
\b0 \
\
This repo contains the code for a Drupal 8 website.\
\
Steps to install locally:\
\

\b 1. 
\b0 Clone the repo to a folder on your computer:\
\

\b git clone git@github.com:ResistanceCalendar/resistance-drupal.git  local_folder_name
\b0 \
\

\b 2. 
\b0 Create a database on your computer. \
\

\b 3. 
\b0 When setting up your local site (with MAMP or whatever you use), best to use PHP 7 (PHP 5.5.9 or higher is required for D8). Note the root folder of the site is the 
\b /web
\b0  folder, so point you local site to that folder:\
\
.git\
.gitignore\
.gitlab-ci.yml\
circle.yml\
composer.json\
composer.lock\
config\
console\
drush\
pantheon.yml\
README.md\
scripts\
tests\
vendor\

\b web
\b0 \
\
