\b 4. 
\b0 Go to the site in your browser and you should be directed to 
\b /core/install.php.
\b0  Go ahead and run the install. In the step where you see the \'91Requirements review\'92 page, you may see some notices, for example 
\i \'91PHP OPcode caching	Not enabled\'92.
\i0  You can fix those if you like, but if there is a \'91continue anyway\'92 link at the bottom you can continue. \
\

\b 5. 
\b0 Enter the DB name, user and pass when asked, then run the install.\
\
6. After install, fill in the rest of the form with anything you want, it will get replaced later when you import the database from the development site.  \
\

\b 7. 
\b0 After finishing the install, you should have a site up and running. \
\

\b 8. 
